      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIN LIDS (8) skirted wide from an outside draw last start and found the front, leading throughout to win (22.21) at this track in a Bottom Up - Maiden over 390m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. PAW XHANI (1) finished well back at Geelong last time when a 6 length fifth (26.33) but scored three back at this track (25.73). Has a good winning strike rate at this journey. Form from her last run is proving strong. A big run wouldn't surprise. PAW QUADE (2) filled a minor placing last start at Geelong behind Little Miss May (23.24) in a T3 RSTW. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to feature. ASTON COSMIC (6) placed last time out so worth considering.",
